{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place milk, egg yolks and seeds from vanilla pod in mixing bowl then cook <b>4 min\/80°C\/speed 6<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add cream and 100 g sugar and cook <b>4 min\/80°C\/speed 2<b>. Pour into shallow, freezer proof containers and leave to cool for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl. Refrigerate ice cream mix for 24 hours to allow mixture to mature.","Churn in an ice cream machine or place in freezer until solid. Meanwhile, prepare rhubarb.","Place remaining 150 g sugar and rhubarb in mixing bowl then cook <b>5-10 min\/80°C\/\/speed <b> (until soft but not falling apart). Transfer to a freezer proof container and allow to cool, then cover and freeze until needed.","When ice cream mixture is set, remove from freezer, tip out and cut into squares (3 cm x 3 cm). Place half the frozen ice cream squares in mixing bowl and churn <b>15 sec\/speed 6<b>. Transfer to a large bowl and set aside.","Place remaining frozen ice cream squares in mixing bowl and churn <b>15 sec\/speed 6<b> then add to bowl with churned ice cream.","Remove rhubarb from freezer, tip out and cut into squares (3 cm x 3 cm). Place half the frozen rhubarb squares in mixing bowl then chop <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>. Add to bowl with churned ice cream.","Place remaining rhubarb in mixing bowl and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b> then add to bowl and stir just enough to create a marble effect. Return to freezer proof containers and freeze for 2 hours or until needed.","Serve in scoops in a bowl or ice cream cone."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["200 g whole milk","6 egg yolks, from large eggs","1 vanilla pod, seeds only, or 1 tsp vanilla bean paste","400 g double cream","250 g caster sugar","700 g rhubarb, cut in pieces (3 cm)"]}],"id":"r104274","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-83Fq2rdSMTc\/XZWe9PopO2I\/AAAAAAAAe8c\/z2EcZyfVyss0vlLvbLOvJxlMFSB3MCFyQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_kxi4vpBiN8sOpx_B.png","title":"Rhubarb Ice Cream","publishedAt":"2016-05-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"7.3 g","fat":"41.1 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"48.5 g","calories":"2479 kJ \/ 593 kcal"},"usefulItems":"freezer proof containers, cling film, refrigerator, freezer","hintsAndTricks":["To remove seeds from vanilla pod easily, split in half lengthways and scrape out seeds with the tip of a knife."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","36h 25m","6 portions"]}